<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122099df-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s720"><num value="720">§ 720.</num><heading> Senate and House Manuals</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each House may order printed as many copies as it desires, of the Senate Manual and of the Rules and Manual of the House of Representatives, even though the cost exceed $500.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122099e0-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1251">82 Stat. 1251</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
